# CSS Class and ID Examples

This file demonstrates the new CSS class and ID syntax in MarkdownUI.

## Basic Examples

Basic class syntax: __.my-class Button|Click Me__

Multiple classes: __.btn.btn-primary.large Button|Primary Button__

ID syntax: __#submit-btn Button|Submit__

Classes and IDs together: __.my-class#my-id Button|Button with class and ID__

## Advanced Examples

With Semantic UI modifiers: __.custom-class.large#special-btn Primary Button|Special Button__

Single underscore syntax: _.red-text#warning Button|Warning Button_

Complex example: __.btn.btn-success#save-form.large Primary Button|Save Form__

## Different Element Types

Custom segment: __.custom-segment#info-section Segment|This is a custom segment__

Custom card: __.custom-card#feature-card Card|Custom styled card__

Custom header: __.custom-header#page-title Large Header|Page Title__

Custom message: __.info-message#status-message Info Message|Status updated successfully__
